{"title_page": "Erik Bjornsen", "text_new": "{{short description|American cross-country skier|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{About|the American cross-country skier|the American football player|Eric Bjornson}}\n{{Infobox skier <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Ski -->\n| name              = Erik Bjornsen\n| image             = 20190227 FIS NWSC Seefeld Men CC 15km Erik Bjornsen 850 4160 (cropped).jpg\n| image_size        = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = Bjornsen at the [[2019 FIS Nordic World Ski Championships|2019 World Championships]]\n| nationality = {{USA}}\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1991|7|14}}\n| birth_place = [[Winthrop, Washington|Winthrop]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]], United States\n| death_date        = <!-- {{death date and age|deathyear|mm|dd|birthyear|mm|dd}} -->\n| death_place       = \n| height            = <!-- X ft X in, X cm or X m (conversions are automatic) -->\n| club              = [[Alaska Pacific University|Alaska Pacific University Nordic Ski Center]]\n| seasons           = [[2012\u201313 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|2013]]\u2013\n| wins              = 0\n| teamwins          = \n| totalpodiums      = 1<!--1 thru 2 December 2018-->\n| teampodiums       = 0\n| events_in_yellow  = <!-- Number of competitions in which an athlete has worn the yellow bib as World Cup points leader -->\n| individual_starts = 116<!--116 thru 20 January 2019-->\n| team_starts       = 10<!--10 thru 27 January 2019-->\n| wcoveralls        = 0 \u2013 ''(50th in [[2017\u201318 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|2018]])''\n| wctitles          =0\n| updated           =28 January, 2019\n| show-medals       = \n| medaltemplates    = \n}}\n'''Erik Bjornsen''' (born July 14, 1991) is an [[United States|American]] [[cross-country skiing|cross-country skier]]. He competed at the [[2014 Winter Olympics]] in [[Sochi, Russia|Sochi]] in the [[Cross-country skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's 30 kilometre skiathlon|30 kilometre skiathlon]] and [[Cross-country skiing at the 2014 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's sprint|sprint]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sochi2014.com/en/athlete-erik-bjornsen |title=Erik Bjornsen \u2013 United States |website=sochi2014.com |publisher=Sochi 2014 Olympics |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704014036/http://www.sochi2014.com/en/athlete-erik-bjornsen |archivedate=July 4, 2014}}</ref> and at the [[2018 Winter Olympics]] in [[Pyeongchang, South Korea|PyeongChang, South Korea]], in men's [[Cross-country skiing at the 2018 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's 30 kilometre skiathlon|30 km skiathon]] and [[Cross-country skiing at the 2018 Winter Olympics \u2013 Men's 15 kilometre freestyle|15 km freestyle]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pyeongchang2018.com/en/game-time/results/OWG2018/en/cross-country-skiing/athlete-profile-n3017869-erik-bjornsen.htm|title=Cross-Country Skiing {{!}} Athlete Profile: Erik BJORNSEN - Pyeongchang 2018 Olympic Winter Games|website=www.pyeongchang2018.com|language=en|access-date=2018-02-20}}</ref>\n\nBjornsen debuted in the World Cup in December 2012. His best result in the world cup was 18th place in the 15&nbsp;km classic in [[Toblach]] in February 2014.\n\nHis sister [[Sadie Bjornsen]] is also a cross-country skier on the [[United States Ski Team]].\n\n==World Cup results==\nAll results are sourced from the [[International Ski Federation|International Ski Federation (FIS)]].<ref name=\"FISprofile\">{{cite web |url=http://data.fis-ski.com/dynamic/athlete-biography.html?sector=CC&listid=&competitorid=139710&type=result |title=Erik BJORNSEN |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |website=FIS-Ski |publisher=International Ski Federation |access-date=3 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n===World Cup standings===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"4\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center; border:grey solid 1px; border-collapse:collapse; background:#ffffff;\"\n! style=\"background-color:#369; color:white; width:60px;\" rowspan=\"2\" |&nbsp;Season&nbsp;\n! style=\"background-color:#369; color:white; width:40px;\" rowspan=\"2\" |&nbsp;Age&nbsp;\n! style=\"background-color:#4180be; color:white;\" colspan=\"3\" |Season Standings\n! style=\"background-color:#4180be; color:white;\" colspan=\"4\" |Ski Tour Standings\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#4180be; color:white; width:75px;\"|Overall\n! style=\"background-color:#4180be; color:white; width:75px;\"|Distance\n! style=\"background-color:#4180be; color:white; width:75px;\"|Sprint\n! style=\"background-color:#4180be; color:white; width:75px;\"|Nordic<br>Opening\n! style=\"background-color:#4180be; color:white; width:75px;\"|Tour de<br>Ski\n! style=\"background-color:#4180be; color:white; width:75px;\"|World Cup<br>Final\n! style=\"background-color:#4180be; color:white; width:75px;\"|Ski Tour<br>Canada\n|-\n| [[2013\u201314 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|2014]] || ''23'' || 133 || 85 || {{Abbr|NC|Not classified}} || {{Abbr|DNP|Did not participate}} || {{Abbr|DNP|Did not participate}} ||  {{Abbr|DNP|Did not participate}} || {{n/a}}\n|-\n| [[2014\u201315 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|2015]] || ''24'' || 137 || {{Abbr|NC|Not classified}} || 82  || 39 || {{Abbr|DNF|Did not finish}} || {{n/a}} || {{n/a}}\n|-\n| [[2015\u201316 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|2016]] || ''25'' || 97 || 67 || 65 || 46 || 46 || {{n/a}} || 42\n|-\n| [[2016\u201317 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|2017]] || ''26'' || 80 || 61 || 80 || 57 || {{Abbr|DNF|Did not finish}}|| 25 || {{n/a}}\n|-\n| [[2017\u201318 FIS Cross-Country World Cup|2018]] || ''27'' || 50 || 38 || 42  || 26 || {{Abbr|DNF|Did not finish}} || 38 || {{n/a}}\n|}\n\n===Individual podiums===\n*1 podium \u2013 (1 {{Abbr|SWC|Stage World Cup}}) <!--1 thru 2 Dec 2018-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"4\" style=\"font-size:95%; text-align:center; border:grey solid 1px; border-collapse:collapse; background:#ffffff;\"\n|- style=\"background:#efefef;\"\n! style=\"background-color:#369; color:white;\"| No.\n! style=\"background-c