{"title_page": "IPhone SE (2nd generation)", "text_new": "{{About|the 2nd generation iPhone SE|its predecessor|iPhone SE (1st generation)}}\n{{pp-move|small=yes}}\n{{short description|thirteenth-generation Apple smartphone}}\n{{lowercase title}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox mobile phone\n| name         = iPhone SE\n| codename     = \n| logo         = IPhone SE (2nd generation) wordmark.svg\n| logosize     = <!-- include \"px\" - Uses users default image size if omitted -->\n| image        = IPhone SE (2nd generation) white vector.svg\n| imagesize    = \n| alt          = \n| caption      = iPhone SE in white, with black bezels\n| brand        = [[Apple Inc.]]\n| manufacturer = \n| slogan       = ''Lots to love. Less to spend.''<ref name=\"Apple official webpage\" >{{Cite web |url = https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/ |title = iPhone SE |website = Apple |language = en-US |access-date = April 15, 2020 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200415160521/https://www.apple.com/iphone-se/ |archive-date = April 15, 2020 |url-status = live }}</ref>\n| serieslabel  = [[History of iPhone|Generation]]\n| series       = 13th\n| modelnumber  = A2275 (United States/Canada)<ref name=\"Official LTE networks\" >{{Cite web|url=https://www.apple.com/iphone/LTE/|title=iPhone - View countries with supported LTE networks|website=Apple|language=en-US|access-date=April 16, 2020}}</ref><br /> A2296 (Global)<ref name=\"Official LTE networks\" /><br />A2298 (China)<ref name=\"Official LTE networks\" /> \n| networks     = \n| released     = {{Start date and age|2020|04|24}}\n| available    = <!-- Country {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} (Retailer) -->\n| discontinued = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| unitssold    = \n| unitsshipped = \n| predecessor  = [[iPhone SE (1st generation)|iPhone SE (1st)]]<br>[[iPhone 8|iPhone 8 / 8 Plus]]\n| successor    =  \n| related      = [[iPhone 11]]<br>[[iPhone 11 Pro|iPhone 11 Pro/Pro Max]]\n| type         = [[Smartphone]]\n| form         = [[